# CityMart Online вЂ” Implementation Steps (3-Tier + Route 53 + ACM + HTTPS)

## 1) Scope (What we are building)
CityMart Online is a mini e-commerce product catalog where customers can:
- Browse products
- View product details
- Submit an order request (no online payment in this lab)

Architecture (3-tier):
- Public ALB (internet-facing) в†’ Web Tier (Nginx) в†’ Internal ALB (private) в†’ App Tier (Apache/PHP) в†’ DB Tier (Aurora/RDS MySQL)

Region/HA:
- Region: eu-west-2 (London)
- 2 AZs: eu-west-2a and eu-west-2b


## 2) Prerequisites
- VPC provisioned with:
  - Public subnets (2) for Public ALB and NAT gateways
  - Private web subnets (2) for Nginx web servers
  - Private app subnets (2) for Apache/PHP backend servers
  - Private DB subnets (2) for Aurora/RDS
- Route tables configured:
  - Public subnets в†’ IGW route for 0.0.0.0/0
  - Private subnets в†’ NAT route for 0.0.0.0/0
- Internet Gateway attached to VPC
- NAT Gateway per AZ (recommended) in public subnets
- Security groups configured:
  - Public ALB SG: allow 80/443 from internet
  - Web tier SG: allow from Public ALB SG
  - Internal ALB SG: allow from Web tier SG
  - App tier SG: allow from Internal ALB SG
  - DB SG: allow 3306 from App tier SG


