## 4) Database Setup (DB Tier)
### 4.1 Create schema
Run:
- `backend/scripts/migrate.sql`

Creates tables:
- `products`
- `customers`
- `orders`
- `order_items`

### 4.2 Seed sample products
Run:
- `backend/scripts/seed.sql`

Recommended execution method (from App server with mysql client installed):
- `mysql -h <DB_ENDPOINT> -u <DB_USER> -p <DB_NAME> < migrate.sql`
- `mysql -h <DB_ENDPOINT> -u <DB_USER> -p <DB_NAME> < seed.sql`

Our DB_ENDPOINT: citymart-database.cdgowmasatge.eu-west-2.rds.amazonaws.com
    DB_USER: admin
    DB_NAME: citymart

Alternative (lab helper):
- `backend/scripts/reset_db.sh` (uses env vars DB_HOST/DB_USER/DB_PASS/DB_PORT)


## 5) Backend Configuration (App Tier: Apache + PHP)
### 5.1 DB connection settings
Update:
- `backend/config/database.php`

Recommended:
- Provide DB connection settings through environment variables:
  - DB_HOST, DB_PORT, DB_NAME, DB_USER, DB_PASS

### 5.2 Deploy backend code
Deploy backend to Apache document root:
- `/var/www/html/`

Expected endpoints:
- `GET  /api/health`
- `GET  /api/products`
- `GET  /api/product?id=1`
- `POST /api/order`

### 5.3 Validate backend locally (on backend server)
- `curl -i http://localhost/api/health`
- `curl -i http://localhost/api/products`


## 6) Web Tier Configuration (Nginx)
### 6.1 Deploy frontend
Copy `frontend/` to Nginx web root:
- `/usr/share/nginx/html/`

### 6.2 Configure reverse proxy (/api) в†’ Internal ALB
Update:
- `nginx/site-citymart.conf`

Requirement:
- Requests to `/api/` must proxy to the Internal ALB:
  - `http://<INTERNAL_ALB_DNS>`

### 6.3 Restart and enable Nginx
- Restart Nginx and ensure it starts on boot.


## 7) Load Balancers and Target Groups
### 7.1 Public ALB (Internet-facing)
- Subnets: 2 public subnets (across 2 AZs)
- Listener:
  - 80 (HTTP) вЂ” recommended: redirect to 443
  - 443 (HTTPS) вЂ” uses ACM certificate
- Target group: Web tier instances (Nginx) in private web subnets
- Health check path: `/index.html` (or a dedicated static path)

### 7.2 Internal ALB (Private)
- Subnets: 2 private app subnets (across 2 AZs)
- Listener:
  - 80 (HTTP)
- Target group: App tier instances (Apache/PHP) in private app subnets
- Health check path: `/api/health`


## 8) Route 53 + ACM + HTTPS (Custom Domain)
Goal: customers access CityMart securely via:
- `https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com`

### 8.1 Create/Confirm a Route 53 Hosted Zone
- Create a hosted zone for your domain (public hosted zone).
- Ensure the domain registrar points to Route 53 name servers (if required).

### 8.2 Request ACM Certificate (Public)
- Request ACM certificate for:
  - `<CUSTOM_DOMAIN>`citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com
  - (optional) `www.citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com`
- Validation method: DNS validation (Route 53 is easiest)

### 8.3 Attach ACM Certificate to the Public ALB
- Configure Public ALB listener 443 (HTTPS) and attach the ACM certificate.
- Configure listener 80 (HTTP) to redirect to HTTPS 443 (recommended).

### 8.4 Create Route 53 ALIAS record to Public ALB
- Create an A/AAAA record (Alias) in the hosted zone:
  - Name: `citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com`
  - Target: Public ALB


## 9) End-to-End Validation (Customer Flow)
From a browser:
1. Open: `https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com/`
2. Products page: `https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com/products.html`
3. Product details: `https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com/product.html?id=1`
4. Checkout: `https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com/checkout.html` (submits to `/api/order`)
5. Success: `https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com/order-success.html`

API validation through the same domain:
- `curl -i https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com/api/health`
- `curl -i https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com`
- `curl -i https://citymart.samuelonyejekwe.com`


## 10) Smoke Tests (Recommended)
Use `deploy/smoke-test.sh` from a machine that can access the public domain:
- Check Home page returns HTTP 200
- Check `/api/health` returns `ok:true`
- Check `/api/products` returns JSON list


## 11) Auto Scaling Notes (Lab-Friendly)
If using ASGs:
- Bake dependencies into AMIs OR use User Data scripts to:
  - Pull application code: `citymart-backend` and `citymart-frontend` from S3 at instance launch
  - Deploy configs + restart services automatically
- Keep DB endpoint and secrets external (env vars / SSM) to avoid rebuilding AMIs for small changes.
